<div class="page-about">

  {%- if settings.icon != blank -%}
    {{
      settings.icon
      | image_url: width: 240
      | image_tag:
        class: 'page-about__icon reveal',
        loading: 'eager',
        alt: 'The Corner Box icon'
    }}
  {%- else -%}
    <img
      class="page-about__icon reveal"
      src="{{ 'icon_the_corner_box.png' | asset_url }}"
      alt="The Corner Box"
      loading="eager"
      width="120"
    >
  {%- endif -%}

  <span class="page-about__label reveal">{{ 'pages.about.label' | t }}</span>

  <div class="page-about__letter">
    <div class="reveal">
      {{ page.content }}
    </div>

    {%- if page.content == blank -%}
      <p class="reveal">
        The Corner Box began as a question: what would it look like to sell vintage comics
        the way a gallery sells prints? Not out of a longbox. Not alphabetized under a
        fluorescent light. But presented — each issue as an object, with context, with care.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal">
        We source selectively. We photograph every copy ourselves. We write condition notes
        that describe what you're actually buying, not just what a grading service decided
        in 2019. The grade matters. So does everything the grade doesn't tell you.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal">
        Our drops are infrequent by design. We don't list anything we wouldn't want to own
        ourselves. Every issue on this site has been through our hands, under our lights,
        and past our own standard before it reaches you.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal">
        If you're serious about collecting, we'd like to earn your attention.
      </p>
      <p class="reveal" style="font-style: italic; color: var(--warm-gray);">
        — The Archivist
      </p>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  <a class="page-about__cta reveal" href="{{ routes.pages_url }}/private-client-list">
    {{ 'pages.about.cta' | t }}
  </a>

</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "About Page",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
